title: For Sale:  Saiga 410 w/30 rd drum mag.
postcontent:
Saiga 410 19" converted. the saiga 410 is a ak47 that is chambered for shotgun shells.

 It comes with a 30rd promag drum, 4rd mag, and whatever ammo I have left by the time its sold(slugs,buckshot mix) Has modified tapco g2 fcg, SAW grip, CSS billet tri rail, detachable optics ount (lucid red dot NOT included) angled trigger guard, and a tapco 6 position stock.

Fired about 150 times, not even fully broken in yet.  Fires/cycles Winchester super x perfectly, from what I've heard no other saiga will cycle super x. That is a testament to the polishing work...

The saiga 410 retails for as low as $655 + $50 shipping + your $30-40 ffl fee, the drum mag retails for 200+. tri-rail $130, the conversion kits retails for $150-200 + shipping.
retail value= $1210.00, Im not trying to get that out of it, but its a ballpark youd need to land in...
Also, if you read up on saigas you will know that saigas usually come with very rough internals out of the box and usually do not cycle all ammo properly, So the bolt carrier group usually needs to be reground and then polished. a service valued at $200+ by your local gunsmith (if you can find one that is experienced, I had a hard time with that one lol). But I sent my parts out to a saiga specialist for polishing and what a difference, cycles like a breeze....

Things to think about before you make an offer... 
local sale only.
best offer takes it home. No trades.
